Overlay patch 0005: the visionOS (xros/xrsimulator) CMake target.

Selected by -DCMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME=visionOS; everything is gated on
SM64_VISIONOS so the iOS target is bit-for-bit unaffected.

What it changes and why (each has a receipt in MEASUREMENTS):
1. OBJCXX added to project() — gfx_metal.mm is Objective-C++.
2. Renderer: iOS keeps USE_GLES/RAPI_GL; visionOS gets
   ENABLE_METAL_BACKEND + SM64_NO_OPENGL and drops both GL defines.
   GL is not merely unused there — every GL entry point is
   API-unavailable in the xrOS SDK, so gfx_opengl.c is excluded from the
   source list and the GL call sites are compiled out (overlay 0002).
3. TARGET_IOS stays defined for visionOS (M-9): it is the fork's OWN
   define, not TargetConditionals' TARGET_OS_IOS (which is 0 on xros), and
   it carries platform.c's correct Documents/bundle-root semantics for
   free. The ROM-drop path needs no change.
4. Deps come from SM64_XROS_DEPS_PREFIX, not lib/*/ios/*.a — the vendored
   prebuilts are Mach-O platform 2 (iOS) and cannot link into an xrOS
   binary (M-5/M-11/D-005). FATAL_ERROR rather than a link-time mystery
   if the prefix is missing.
5. -framework OpenGLES dropped for visionOS.
6. Device family 7 + XROS_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET (CMake emits
   IPHONEOS_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET, which Xcode ignores for xros).
7. SDL2 gets the visionOS compat patch alongside the fork's existing iOS
   gamepad fix, through the fork's own git-apply mechanism. The two
   compose in either order — proven on this tree, both directions (M-9).
8. Info.plist: a visionOS-specific plist via SM64_VISIONOS_PLIST.
9. Signing team via SM64_DEVELOPMENT_TEAM (default "" = iOS unchanged).
   The vendored CMakeLists hardcodes XCODE_ATTRIBUTE_DEVELOPMENT_TEAM ""
   as a TARGET property. Xcode target-level build settings BEAT
   project-level ones, and CMAKE_XCODE_ATTRIBUTE_* writes the project
   level — so passing -DCMAKE_XCODE_ATTRIBUTE_DEVELOPMENT_TEAM on the
   command line is silently overridden by the empty target value and the
   device build dies with "Signing for 'sm64coopdx' requires a
   development team." Measured, not reasoned: the generated pbxproj
   carries DEVELOPMENT_TEAM = 57G8J46Z2T at project level AND
   DEVELOPMENT_TEAM = "" at target level, and the build fails (M-27).
   The sim build never hit this because it sets CODE_SIGNING_ALLOWED=NO.
10. INSTALL_PATH/SKIP_INSTALL on the target, or `xcodebuild archive`
   produces an archive with an EMPTY Products/ (CMake defaults every
   target to INSTALL_PATH = ""). -exportArchive then rejects a perfectly
   valid export method with `expected one {} but found debugging` —
   an empty set of distribution methods, because Xcode cannot classify
   an archive containing no app. Same target-vs-project precedence trap
   as item 9 (M-28).

DELIBERATELY NOT DONE — the CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME flip. Shipwright's overlay
0022 flips CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME back to "iOS" after every project() because
ITS tree dispatches on STREQUAL "iOS" at 16+ sites. This tree does not:
it dispatches on its own TARGET_IOS option. Flipping here would be
actively harmful — SDL 2.32.10 self-detects visionOS in
cmake/sdlplatform.cmake (`set(${SDL_CMAKE_PLATFORM} TRUE)` => VISIONOS),
and all 13 of its platform conditionals in CMakeLists.txt are OR-groups
containing VISIONOS. Leaving CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME alone is what makes that
detection fire. Proven, not argued: the configured build reports
"Platform: visionOS" and compiles src/misc/ios/SDL_sysurl.m (NOT
src/misc/macosx, which is the failure the charter's trap describes).

BUT `set(IOS 1)` IS STILL REQUIRED — for a different reason than the
charter's, and I only found it by hitting it. SDL2's CMakeLists.txt
consistently ORs VISIONOS into its platform groups, but
cmake/sdlchecks.cmake:1259 does NOT:

    if(IOS OR TVOS)
      list(APPEND SOURCE_FILES ${SDL2_SOURCE_DIR}/src/hidapi/ios/hid.m)
      set(SDL_FRAMEWORK_COREBLUETOOTH 1)
    endif()

That is the ONLY bare IOS use in sdlchecks.cmake. With SDL_HIDAPI on
(its default), src/hidapi/*.c compiles and references PLATFORM_hid_*, but
no platform implementation is selected on visionOS => 17 undefined
symbols at app link (_PLATFORM_hid_init, _PLATFORM_hid_read, ...). A real
SDL 2.32.10 gap, not our misconfiguration.

So the trap is real but its mechanism is the opposite of the charter's
telling: Shipwright's flip set IOS=1 as a side effect and thereby MASKED
this hidapi gap, which is why its notes attribute set(IOS 1) to the
misc/macosx source selection. Setting IOS 1 alongside an unflipped
CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME gets both right: sdlchecks:1259 fires (hidapi/ios/hid.m
+ CoreBluetooth, exactly as the proven iOS build does), and the
CMakeLists OR-groups are unaffected because they already matched on
VISIONOS. Verified src/hidapi/ios/hid.m compiles clean for
arm64-apple-xros2.0-simulator before adopting it.

--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -1,6 +1,30 @@
 cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.21)
-project(sm64coopdx C CXX OBJC)
+# OBJCXX: the Metal rendering backend (src/pc/gfx/gfx_metal.mm) is Objective-C++.
+project(sm64coopdx C CXX OBJC OBJCXX)
 
+# visionOS is selected with -DCMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME=visionOS (+ an xros/xrsimulator
+# sysroot). NOTE: we deliberately do NOT flip CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME back to "iOS"
+# here. This tree dispatches on its own TARGET_IOS option rather than on
+# CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME, so there is nothing to appease — and SDL2 2.32.10 relies on
+# seeing "visionOS" to self-detect (cmake/sdlplatform.cmake sets VISIONOS TRUE,
+# which every one of its platform conditionals ORs against). Flipping the name
+# would silently send SDL down its macOS source list.
+if(CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME STREQUAL "visionOS")
+    set(SM64_VISIONOS 1)
+    # set(IOS 1): CMake's Platform/visionOS-Initialize.cmake sets NO platform
+    # variable at all (its iOS counterpart sets IOS 1), and SDL2's
+    # cmake/sdlchecks.cmake:1259 gates its hidapi platform backend on a bare
+    # `if(IOS OR TVOS)` — the one place SDL forgets to OR in VISIONOS. Without
+    # this, src/hidapi/*.c still compiles and calls PLATFORM_hid_*, but no
+    # implementation is selected => 17 undefined symbols at app link. This is
+    # the ONLY bare IOS use in sdlchecks.cmake, and SDL2's CMakeLists platform
+    # groups already match on VISIONOS, so this flips exactly that one site and
+    # nothing else. (src/hidapi/ios/hid.m compiles clean for xros; it brings in
+    # CoreBluetooth, which this target already links.)
+    set(IOS 1)
+    message(STATUS "sm64coopdx: targeting visionOS (Metal backend, no OpenGL)")
+endif()
+
 set(CMAKE_C_STANDARD 11)
 set(CMAKE_CXX_STANDARD 17)
 
@@ -28,8 +52,6 @@
     IMMEDIATELOAD
     DYNOS
     COOP
-    USE_GLES
-    RAPI_GL=1
     WAPI_SDL2=1
