+# Signing team. This has to be a cache variable rather than
+# -DCMAKE_XCODE_ATTRIBUTE_DEVELOPMENT_TEAM: the DEVELOPMENT_TEAM below is a
+# TARGET property, and in Xcode target-level build settings override
+# project-level ones (which is where CMAKE_XCODE_ATTRIBUTE_* lands). The
+# command-line value is accepted, written to the project level, and then
+# silently beaten by the empty target value -> "Signing for 'sm64coopdx'
+# requires a development team". Default "" keeps the iOS target unchanged.
+set(SM64_DEVELOPMENT_TEAM "" CACHE STRING "Apple Developer team ID used to sign the app")
